{smcl}
{com}{sf}{ul off}{txt}
{com}. 
. * =====================================================================
. * STEP 0: Protocol specification (Hernan 7-component framework)
. * =====================================================================
. * The protocol should be defined BEFORE any analysis, following
. * Hernan & Robins (2016). This is unique to the tte package.
. 
. noisily tte, protocol
{txt}
{hline 70}
{res}tte{txt} - Target Trial Emulation for Stata
Version 1.0.4
{hline 70}

{bf:Hernan & Robins (2016) 7-Component Framework}

  Every target trial emulation must specify:

  {result:1. Eligibility criteria}
     Who is eligible to enter the trial at each time point?
     Example: Age >= 18, no prior outcome event, >= 1 year follow-up

  {result:2. Treatment strategies}
     What treatments are being compared?
     Example: Initiate drug A vs. do not initiate drug A

  {result:3. Treatment assignment}
     How is treatment assigned in the observational data?
     Example: Patients assigned at each eligible period based on
     physician decision (emulates randomization at baseline)

  {result:4. Start of follow-up (time zero)}
     When does follow-up begin for each emulated trial?
     Example: Start of each eligible period (eligibility = assignment)

  {result:5. Outcome}
     What is the outcome of interest?
     Example: All-cause mortality within 5 years

  {result:6. Causal contrast}
     ITT (intention-to-treat) or PP (per-protocol)?
     ITT: analyze as initially assigned regardless of switching
     PP: censor at deviation, reweight with IPTW

  {result:7. Statistical analysis}
     What model and estimation approach?
     Example: Pooled logistic regression with robust SE,
     clustered by individual, adjusted for confounders

{hline 70}
{bf:Document your protocol with} {cmd:tte_protocol}:

  {cmd:tte_protocol, eligibility("Age >= 18, no prior event")}
      {cmd:treatment("Initiate drug vs no drug")}
      {cmd:assignment("At each eligible period")}
      {cmd:followup_start("Start of eligible period")}
      {cmd:outcome("All-cause mortality")}
      {cmd:causal_contrast("Per-protocol effect")}
      {cmd:analysis("Pooled logistic with IPCW")}
      {cmd:export(protocol.xlsx) format(excel) replace}

{hline 70}

{com}. 
. noisily tte_protocol, ///
>     eligibility("Eligible at period start (eligible == 1); no prior outcome") ///
>     treatment("Initiate treatment vs. do not initiate treatment") ///
>     assignment("At each eligible period, based on observed treatment decision") ///
>     followup_start("Start of the period when eligibility criteria are met") ///
>     outcome("Binary outcome event (outcome == 1)") ///
>     causal_contrast("Intention-to-treat (ITT) and per-protocol (PP)") ///
>     analysis("Pooled logistic regression with robust SE, clustered by id") ///
>     export("`pkg_dir'/protocol.xlsx") format(excel) replace
{txt}
{hline 70}
{res}Target Trial Protocol Specification
{txt}(Hernan & Robins 7-component framework)
{hline 70}

{bf:1. Eligibility criteria}
   Eligible at period start (eligible == 1); no prior outcome

{bf:2. Treatment strategies}
   Initiate treatment vs. do not initiate treatment

{bf:3. Treatment assignment}
   At each eligible period, based on observed treatment decision

{bf:4. Start of follow-up (time zero)}
   Start of the period when eligibility criteria are met

{bf:5. Outcome}
   Binary outcome event (outcome == 1)

{bf:6. Causal contrast}
   Intention-to-treat (ITT) and per-protocol (PP)

{bf:7. Statistical analysis}
   Pooled logistic regression with robust SE, clustered by id

{hline 70}
{res}{txt}file {bf:tte/demo/protocol.xlsx} saved
{res}{txt}file {bf:tte/demo/protocol.xlsx} saved
{res}{txt}file {bf:tte/demo/protocol.xlsx} saved
{res}{txt}file {bf:tte/demo/protocol.xlsx} saved
{res}{txt}file {bf:tte/demo/protocol.xlsx} saved
{res}{txt}file {bf:tte/demo/protocol.xlsx} saved
{res}{txt}file {bf:tte/demo/protocol.xlsx} saved
{res}{txt}Protocol exported to: {res}tte/demo/protocol.xlsx
{txt}
{com}. 
. * =====================================================================
. * ANALYSIS 1: Intention-to-Treat (ITT)
. * =====================================================================
. * ITT ignores treatment switching — everyone analyzed as initially assigned.
. * No weights needed. Compare results to R TrialEmulation reference.
. 
. noisily display _newline
{res}

{txt}
{com}. noisily display as text "ITT ANALYSIS (R TrialEmulation benchmark)"
{res}{txt}ITT ANALYSIS (R TrialEmulation benchmark)

{com}. 
. use tte/demo/data/trial_example.dta, clear
{txt}(R TrialEmulation trial_example (503 patients, 48400 obs))

{com}. 
. tte_prepare, id(id) period(period) treatment(treatment) ///
>     outcome(outcome) eligible(eligible) ///
>     covariates(catvara catvarb catvarc nvara nvarb nvarc) ///
>     estimand(ITT)
{txt}
{hline 70}
{res}tte_prepare{txt} - Data Preparation
